<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1843,2011]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,391]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="42" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,293,1843,1868]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Surface of vertex, pronotum and scutellum shagreen (Plate I: A). Head wider than pronotum. Vertex subtriangular, flat, anterior margin foliaceous, lateral margins oblique and almost in line with outer margins of eye, ocellus near anterior margin of head, far from eye, eye projecting posterad beyond anterior angles of pronotum (Plate I: A–C); genae deeply notched below eye, extended beyond anteclypeus (Plate I: D). Pronotum distinctly carinate laterally, more than twice as broad as long (Plate I: A–C). Forewing passing abdominal apex, appendix absent, apices not overlapping, texture coriaceous, veins distinctly elevated (Plate I: A). Hindwing reduced. Profemur setal row AV with 13–15 similar peg-like setae; AM1 present (
<figureCitation box="[701,828,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Figs 2A–B</figureCitation>
). Foretibia rounded in cross section, dorsal macrosetal formula 1+1 (
<figureCitation box="[309,600,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Figs 2C &amp; 2D, 2E &amp; 2F</figureCitation>
). Hind femur setal formula 2+0 (
<figureCitation box="[984,1076,223,247]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia setal row AD with approximately 6–7 long stout setae and 2–5 shorter setae between each long seta (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1134,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
); AV with apical seta larger than basal (
<figureCitation box="[278,367,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
); pecten with several normal macrosetae and 2 platellae (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1081,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
); PD with appproximately 9–11 macrosetae, 0–2 shorter setae between each long seta, hardly as long as those of AD (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1158,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[159,1385,193,1926]" captionTargetId="figure-83@4.[151,1436,149,1956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: front femur, anterior view; C &amp; E: left front tibia, anterodorsal view; D &amp; F: left front tibia, posterodorsal view; G: apex of hind femur, dorsal view; H: left hind tibia, anterior view (without apical row); I: pecten of left hind tibia, anterior view; J: left hind tibia, posterior view (without PV and apical row)." pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2J</figureCitation>
). Hind tarsomere I nearly parallel-sided, with dorsoapical pair of setae, and ventral scattered setae, and 4 patellae in pecten.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="1" pageNumber="42" startId="1.[151,249,1980,2003]" targetBox="[219,1350,432,1961]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1980,2033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
