<taxonomicName authority="Pruthi. A" authorityName="Pruthi. A" authorityYear="1930" box="[283,616,1980,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gurawa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minorcephala">
<emphasis box="[283,513,1980,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Gurawa minorcephala</emphasis>
Pruthi. A
</taxonomicName>
–B: male pygofer side, lateral view; C: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, caudal and lateral view, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1822,1875]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,1822,1845]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">PLATE I.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pruthi. A" authorityName="Pruthi. A" authorityYear="1930" box="[268,605,1822,1844]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gurawa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minorcephala">
<emphasis box="[268,500,1822,1844]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Gurawa minorcephala</emphasis>
Pruthi. A
</taxonomicName>
–B: habitus, dorsal view; C: habitus, lateral view; D: face; E: the end of female abdomen, ventral view; F: first valvula; G: detail of first valvula; H: second valvula; I: detail of second valvula.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1919,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="43">
Male pygofer without macrosetae, basolateral cleft absent or not membranous (
<figureCitation box="[1104,1233,1919,1943]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,249,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[219,1350,432,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-180@1.[188,1398,411,1983]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: male pygofer side, lateral view; C: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, caudal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Figs 1A–B</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation box="[159,248,1955,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,249,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[219,1350,432,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-180@1.[188,1398,411,1983]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: male pygofer side, lateral view; C: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, caudal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate triangular, short, without macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[893,981,1955,1979]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,249,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[219,1350,432,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-180@1.[188,1398,411,1983]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: male pygofer side, lateral view; C: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, caudal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Connective with anterior arms closely appressed with distinct stem (
<figureCitation box="[482,568,1991,2015]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,249,1980,2003]" captionTargetBox="[219,1350,432,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-180@1.[188,1398,411,1983]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Gurawa minorcephala Pruthi. A–B: male pygofer side, lateral view; C: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F &amp; G: aedeagus, caudal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="2" pageNumber="43">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
First valvula dorsal sculpturing granulose to maculose, slightly submarginal for most of length (Plate I: F–G). Second valvula abruptly broadened ~1/2 its length from base, with small obliquely triangular dorsal teeth over nearly apical half (Plate I: H–I). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,259,284]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,429,260,284]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">China</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry box="[441,502,260,284]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">India</collectingCountry>
; Oriental Region.
</paragraph>
